1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Be3 dxe4 4. Nd2 Nf6 5. f3 exf3 6. Ngxf3 Be7 7. Bd3 Nd5 {Stockfish's defence: hit the e3-bishop before castling. Rare below 2000, but the critical test of the gambit.} (7... b6 {The fianchetto plan - met by a change of address for the white king.} 8. Qe2 {Against ...b6 White castles long: the b7-bishop will stare at a well-defended knight while the h-pawn runs at the black king.} Bb7 9. O-O-O Nbd7 (9... O-O 10. h4 {The point of opposite castling: every h-pawn step is a developing move. Engine -0.4, but White scores fine here and the play is one-directional.} Nbd7 11. Rhf1 Rc8 12. Ne5 {Standing tall on e5: 12...Nxe5 13.dxe5 would hit the f6-knight and open the d-file toward d7. A classic attacking tableau.}) (9... Nc6 10. a3 {Quietly denying ...Nb4 forever. White continues Ne5, h4-h5 and g4 with a straightforward initiative.}) 10. Ne5 {Occupying the hole: if 10...Nxe5 11.dxe5 the f6-knight is hit and White gains another tempo.} O-O 11. Rhf1 c5 12. h4 {The storm begins. Engine: roughly -0.3 for the pawn, but practice favours White heavily - this position scores 60 percent.}) 8. Qe2 {Calm: let Black take on e3. The recapture strengthens White's centre control, and the d1-square is freed for long castling.} Nxe3 9. Qxe3 O-O (9... Nd7 10. O-O-O Nf6 (10... c5 {The engine's best try: counterplay before White's attack exists.} 11. Rhe1 {Centralising with threats against e6; engine -0.5, the gambit's honest price, but Black must keep finding accurate moves with less space.}) 11. Ne5 {The familiar clamp. White continues Qf3 or h4 next; equal by engine, far easier for White.}) (9... Nc6 10. c3 O-O 11. O-O-O {Opposite kings again: h4, g4 and Ne5 write the plan by themselves. From here White scores 64 percent.}) 10. O-O-O {Opposite-side castling - the h-pawn becomes a battering ram and every tempo matters.} Nd7 (10... Nc6 11. c3 Bf6 {Eyeing d4 - but the bishop becomes a target.} 12. g4 {+1.7. The storm hits first:} e5 13. g5 {and the bishop is pushed home while the kingside opens. White wins the race.}) 11. h4 {Engine -0.3; humans score 61 percent for White. Plan: h5, Ng5 or g4-g5, with Rhf1 always useful. Black's extra pawn is a spectator.} *

[Event "Alapin Gambit - Ch 3: Accepted, 6th-move alternatives and 5...Nd5"]
